        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 6:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " “alms” and “righteousness” occur as alternative readings. We have “alms” in the Authorised Version, “righteousness” in the Revised Version. To this day the Jews call alms ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ts’dâkah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“righteousness.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
